        "author_association": "OWNER",
        "body": "Hi lionel,\r\n\r\nthis issue seems related to the calculation of the distance raster. Can you please check if your study area of interest (+buffer) contains at least one feature of what you want to test for (since you use the default (roads, rivers, cities, airpoirts). If this is not the case, you can:\r\n\r\n1. provide your own, more detailed reference data via the `gaz` argument. I suspect that maybe airports might be the problem, so you can also just resample the references data to exclude airports:\r\n\r\n```\r\nred_gaz <- list(cities = sampbias::cities,\r\n                      rivers = sampbias::waterbodies, \r\n                      roads = sampbias::roads)\r\n\r\ncalculate_bias(x, gaz = red_gaz)\r\n```\r\n\r\n2. Increase the buffer, so that the study area includes  at least one feature of any kind.\r\n\r\nPlease let me know if that solved the problem.\r\n\r\nCheers,\r\n\r\nAlex"
    },
